'''Xaver Schlager''' ({{IPA|de|ˈksaːvɐ ˈʃlaːɡɐ}};<ref>{{cite book|first1=Stefan|last1=Kleiner|first2=Ralf|last2=Knöbl|year=2015|orig-year=First published 1962|title=Das Aussprachewörterbuch|trans-title=The Pronunciation Dictionary|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=T6vWCgAAQBAJ|language=de|edition=7th|location=Berlin|publisher=Dudenverlag|isbn=978-3-411-04067-4|pages=764, 911}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|first1=Eva-Maria|last1=Krech|first2=Eberhard|last2=Stock|first3=Ursula|last3=Hirschfeld|first4=Lutz Christian|last4=Anders|title=Deutsches Aussprachewörterbuch|trans-title=German Pronunciation Dictionary|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=E-1tr_oVkW4C&q=deutsches+ausspracheworterbuch|language=de|year=2009|publisher=Walter de Gruyter|location=Berlin|isbn=978-3-11-018202-6|pages=905, 1062}}</ref> born 28 September 1997) is an Austrian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] for {{German football updater|RBLeipzi}} club [[RB Leipzig]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].

==Club career==
===Red Bull Salzburg===
After playing for the youth team of SC St. Valentin, Schlager joined the [[FC Red Bull Salzburg]] Academy in 2011, where he played in all teams. In 2015, Schlager was transferred to FC Liefering, the feeder team of FC Red Bull Salzburg.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rbleipzig.com/en/news/2022-2023/xaver-schlager-joins-rbl/ |title=Xaver Schlager joins RB Leipzig! |date=17 June 2022 |publisher=Red Bull Salzburg |access-date=29 June 2024 |archive-date=17 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220617224352/https://rbleipzig.com/en/news/2022-2023/xaver-schlager-joins-rbl/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

During the [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League|2017–18 season]], Salzburg had their best ever European campaign. They finished top of their Europa League group, for a record fourth time, before beating [[Real Sociedad]] and [[Borussia Dortmund]] thus making their first ever appearance in the UEFA Europa League semi-final.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/0244-0e98bb008042-c1ca7adedb30-1000--salzburg-v-marseille-background/|title=Salzburg v Marseille background|website=UEFA|date=27 April 2018}}</ref> On 3 May 2018, he played in the [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League knockout phase#Semi-finals|Europa League semi-finals]] as [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] beat Salzburg 3–2 on aggregate to secure a place in the [[2018 UEFA Europa League Final|final]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=FC Red Bull Salzburg 2–1 Marseille|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/43998194|website=[[BBC Sport]]|date=3 May 2018}}</ref>

===VfL Wolfsburg===
On the 26 June 2019, Schlager signed for [[Bundesliga]] club [[VfL Wolfsburg]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Verstärkung für das Mittelfeld|url=https://www.vfl-wolfsburg.de/newsdetails/news-detail/detail/news/verstaerkung-fuer-das-mittelfeld/|website=VfL Wolfsburg|date=26 June 2019|access-date=28 June 2019|language=de}}</ref> During his time with Wolfsburg,  Schlager made 81 appearances in all competitions, including 69 in the Bundesliga.<ref name=RBLS /> He missed 20 league matches through injury during his [[2021–22 VfL Wolfsburg season|final season]], but still averaged 27 pressures per game whilst producing a goal and two assists.<ref name=RBLS />

===RB Leipzig===
On 17 June 2022, Schlager joined Bundesliga rivals [[RB Leipzig]], after the club activated a release clause in his Wolfsburg contract. He signed a contract until 2026.<ref>{{Cite web|title=RB Leipzig recruit Austria's Schlager from Wolfsburg|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/rb-leipzig-recruit-austrias-schlager-142007613.html|website=Yahoo Sports|date=17 June 2022|access-date=17 June 2022|archive-date=12 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220712172129/https://sports.yahoo.com/rb-leipzig-recruit-austrias-schlager-142007613.html|url-status=dead}}</ref>  Schlager helped Leipzig to win the [[2023 DFB-Pokal final|German Cup]] and [[2023 DFL-Supercup|German Super Cup]] in 2023, starting the latter, coming on as substitute in the German Cup Final. In early May 2024, Schlager was playing against Hoffenheim, when he was substituted off with an injury. Later tests confirmed that his ACL was torn, and underwent surgery, therefore missing the European Championship in the summer.

==International career==
On 23 March 2018, Schlager debuted for the [[Austria national football team|Austrian senior squad]] in a friendly 3–0 victory over [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Xaver Schlager: "Der Teamchef soll mich kritisieren"|url=https://www.sn.at/sport/fussball/nationalteam/xaver-schlager-der-teamchef-soll-mich-kritisieren-25860595|website=[[Salzburger Nachrichten]]|date=26 March 2018|language=de}}</ref> The same year on 18 September, he scored his first goal in a [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League]] match against [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Erstes Länderspiel-Tor: Schlager zuckt nicht aus|trans-title=First international goal: Schlager doesn't flinch|url=https://www.laola1.at/de/red/fussball/oefb-nationalteam/a-team/news/erstes-laenderspiel-tor--xaver-schlager-zuckt-nicht-aus/|website=[[Laola1]]|date=18 November 2019|language=de}}</ref>

